President Donald J. Trump spoke with Governor Kenneth Mapp of the U.S. Virgin Islands to express his support for the territory as it prepares for Hurricane Irma. The President confirmed that the Federal Government has been actively preparing for the hurricane response, while also supporting the states of Texas and Louisiana in the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey. FEMA will continue to coordinate with the U.S. Virgin Islands' emergency management staff and work with other federal partners to aid the territory's efforts.